762
01:32:42,920 --> 01:32:44,940
Personally, I prefer something more
adventurous...

763
01:32:45,690 --> 01:32:46,880
...like wild life photography

764
01:32:47,260 --> 01:32:48,520
You like photography?

765
01:32:49,490 --> 01:32:53,860
Mum says the first word I said
wasn't Papa or Mama...

766
01:32:54,060 --> 01:32:54,890
It was camera!

767
01:32:59,170 --> 01:32:59,630
I'm Steve

768
01:33:00,700 --> 01:33:02,330
Steve? - Satyadev Mehta

769
01:33:05,110 --> 01:33:08,700
I've organized a car for you.
I'll get your trolley

770
01:33:11,180 --> 01:33:13,040
Okay Shalini, I'll take your leave.
Bye, Mahesh

771
01:33:14,850 --> 01:33:20,340
Here's my card. If you need
anything in Sydney, call me

772
01:33:47,280 --> 01:33:50,050
Well, I'd better leave now.
I'm sure you want to rest

773
01:33:50,390 --> 01:33:52,350
I'll send the driver to pick you
up tomorrow

774
01:34:15,940 --> 01:34:19,280
Yes, I'll tell Mr. Mehta

775
01:34:46,810 --> 01:34:49,300
Dad wants you to send him
a copy of the new contract

776
01:34:52,680 --> 01:34:54,010
You are coming to the meeting
tomorrow, aren't you?

777
01:34:55,380 --> 01:34:57,680
Can you give me our transaction
file?

778
01:34:57,950 --> 01:34:59,580
I'd like to know a little more about
them before the meeting

779
01:34:59,920 --> 01:35:01,390
I'll send you the file right away

780
01:35:07,260 --> 01:35:08,730
Is there a good restaurant around
here?

781
01:35:35,020 --> 01:35:37,050
Being alone in a new city
can be so boring

782
01:35:37,830 --> 01:35:39,090
But you aren't alone!

783
01:35:39,790 --> 01:35:40,990
Who said I was bored?

784
01:35:45,500 --> 01:35:47,430
Who'd have thought that
someday you

785
01:35:47,640 --> 01:35:49,500
and me would be sitting
here like friends

786
01:35:52,110 --> 01:35:53,130
Especially after all that happened...

787
01:35:56,280 --> 01:35:56,900
So how is Rohit?

788
01:35:58,450 --> 01:36:00,880
He's fine. I spoke to him
this morning

789
01:36:01,980 --> 01:36:05,540
I told him I met you on the flight
and...

790
01:36:09,090 --> 01:36:10,950
And he doesn't like you meeting
me! Right?

791
01:36:16,330 --> 01:36:18,200
But you're here.
Why?

792
01:36:18,400 --> 01:36:20,730
Akash, you don't know Rohit.

793
01:36:21,040 --> 01:36:23,200
He doesn't like me meeting
any boys

794
01:36:26,040 --> 01:36:27,270
But Rohit is a good guy

795
01:36:28,210 --> 01:36:33,080
He has a few faults but then,
don't we all. Me... you...

796
01:36:34,020 --> 01:36:36,010
Faults... and me!

797
01:36:38,620 --> 01:36:39,980
So tell me about yourself

798
01:36:41,560 --> 01:36:42,420
What do you want to know?

799
01:36:48,600 --> 01:36:51,690
Of course I have. But not for
more than 2 weeks

800
01:36:52,830 --> 01:36:55,030
Then there's another girlfriend...
another 2 weeks...

801
01:36:55,900 --> 01:36:56,700
And then another...

802
01:36:56,900 --> 01:37:00,840
stop! I understand how your
girlfriend system works

803
01:37:01,210 --> 01:37:03,040
What I don't understand is...
why?

804
01:37:04,410 --> 01:37:07,810
The fact is, I've seen many of my
friends with their "beloveds"

805
01:37:08,250 --> 01:37:10,610
They have everything but love
for each other

806
01:37:12,250 --> 01:37:13,740
That's why I think I am better off
as I am

807
01:37:14,020 --> 01:37:16,990
No questions... no answers

808
01:37:18,460 --> 01:37:21,190
I don't ask Rohit questions,
nor do I demand answers

809
01:37:21,400 --> 01:37:23,960
But he asks questions.
He demands answers

810
01:37:25,300 --> 01:37:27,630
I never said it's always
the girl's fault

811
01:37:28,340 --> 01:37:31,670
But relationships just get like that.
Start with joy and end in grief

812
01:37:32,740 --> 01:37:36,700
I see! So this is the result of
an end in grief

813
01:37:38,110 --> 01:37:39,880
Now I've understood your
2 weeks formula!

814
01:37:40,080 --> 01:37:41,210
No! It's nothing of the sort

815
01:37:41,950 --> 01:37:44,920
I have consciously decided not to
fall in love and ruin my life

816
01:37:46,450 --> 01:37:49,250
But love isn't about decisions.
It just happens

817
01:37:49,960 --> 01:37:50,920
Then I don't let it happen to me

818
01:37:52,130 --> 01:37:54,420
Give it some time. I'm sure
it will some day

819
01:37:56,960 --> 01:37:59,590
Why? Are you proposing?

820
01:38:09,140 --> 01:38:10,270
How was your day?

821
01:38:14,820 --> 01:38:15,610
Akash is nuts

822
01:38:39,410 --> 01:38:40,870
Turn it down guys.
It's my wife-to-be

823
01:38:43,740 --> 01:38:44,370
How are you?

824
01:38:45,080 --> 01:38:46,380
Hopefully a little less drunk

825
01:38:49,250 --> 01:38:51,220
Did you get my message?
Where were you?

826
01:38:52,250 --> 01:38:53,380
I met Akash for lunch

827
01:38:57,420 --> 01:39:00,880
I told you not to meet him!
Why don't you listen to me?

828
01:39:03,600 --> 01:39:05,390
Are you yelling at me in front
of your friends?

829
01:39:10,940 --> 01:39:14,400
I am coming there. It'll take some
time but I will be there

830
01:39:16,110 --> 01:39:18,410
As you wish, Rohit. Bye

831
01:39:25,050 --> 01:39:28,350
Pooja, I was in the neighbourhood
and I thought...

832
01:39:30,220 --> 01:39:32,520
Pooja, if you aren't doing
anything else...

833
01:39:35,400 --> 01:39:37,860
Pooja, I was in the neighbour...

834
01:39:39,730 --> 01:39:41,030
Bye mom, I'll call later

835
01:40:22,610 --> 01:40:23,910
Fine. And you?

836
01:40:27,280 --> 01:40:29,750
Subodh, this is Sameer.
Sameer, this is Subodh

837
01:40:40,960 --> 01:40:42,090
Are you waiting for someone?

838
01:40:42,800 --> 01:40:46,100
Yes. But it seems like
they won't show up now

839
01:40:53,370 --> 01:40:55,500
So tell me... what's the plan
after dinner?

840
01:40:56,550 --> 01:40:57,170
No plan

841
01:40:59,050 --> 01:41:00,170
Come on, let's do something

842
01:41:02,550 --> 01:41:03,180
What say, Subodh?

843
01:41:04,220 --> 01:41:06,020
I'm sorry. I've made it a habit
to sleep by 10

844
01:41:08,220 --> 01:41:10,020
One night won't change
your habit

845
01:41:10,730 --> 01:41:12,700
Come on, pal. Anyway,
it's Sunday tomorrow

846
01:41:13,060 --> 01:41:15,860
I know. Thing is I've to wake up at
5 and do Yoga

847
01:41:16,570 --> 01:41:19,540
Then some jogging and breakfast
at 8 sharp

848
01:41:20,900 --> 01:41:21,870
And since it's Sunday...

849
01:41:22,410 --> 01:41:24,200
...we spend the day at Kumar uncle's
beach house

850
01:41:27,510 --> 01:41:27,980
I'll be right back

851
01:41:34,220 --> 01:41:35,680
It's time for his bathroom break,
right?

852
01:41:36,390 --> 01:41:38,680
He isn't that bad

853
01:41:42,730 --> 01:41:44,020
So where are you off to?

854
01:41:44,730 --> 01:41:45,190
Let's see...

855
01:41:46,060 --> 01:41:50,190
If Time Table doesn't want to
come, may be you can join me

856
01:41:51,400 --> 01:41:52,370
I'm sure I can...

857
01:41:59,740 --> 01:42:01,040
If I call you sometime...

858
01:42:18,990 --> 01:42:21,460
Wow! What're we celebrating?

859
01:42:22,670 --> 01:42:23,290
You don't remember?

860
01:42:24,670 --> 01:42:28,470
It was on this day five months ago
that I told you what I felt for you

861
01:42:42,250 --> 01:42:43,880
To Subodh and Pooja!

862
01:42:50,090 --> 01:42:51,560
What's the situation like?
- Pretty intense

863
01:42:56,330 --> 01:42:56,960
Really, Mahesh

864
01:42:58,330 --> 01:43:02,290
There were such intense scenes
in the film! So moving...

865
01:43:03,840 --> 01:43:04,810
Please cut out the performance

866
01:43:05,170 --> 01:43:08,300
And forgive me for taking you
to see such a good film!

867
01:43:09,680 --> 01:43:10,800
You see! That's my biggest problem

868
01:43:11,680 --> 01:43:12,980
I can't bear watching good films

869
01:43:14,350 --> 01:43:17,980
Yes. You only like those
wham bang action films

870
01:43:18,520 --> 01:43:19,990
Anyway, that's all you can
understand...

871
01:43:20,520 --> 01:43:23,320
...because they don't require you
to use your brains or heart!

872
01:43:24,360 --> 01:43:26,160
You need plenty of brains for
these love stories

873
01:43:27,030 --> 01:43:29,660
She sits here shedding tears,
he sits there sighing...

874
01:43:30,870 --> 01:43:32,160
...what's all this lovey- dovey
stuff about anyway!

875
01:43:33,700 --> 01:43:34,500
You won't understand

876
01:43:36,370 --> 01:43:37,500
What're you doing man, let's go

877
01:43:57,230 --> 01:44:00,530
Wonder why
people fall in love

878
01:44:04,900 --> 01:44:08,200
Wonder why people
are ready to die for someone

879
01:44:12,410 --> 01:44:15,710
Wonder why
people fall in love

880
01:44:16,250 --> 01:44:19,540
Wonder why people
are ready to die for someone

881
01:44:20,250 --> 01:44:24,210
Wonder why,
Oh wonder why...

882
01:44:27,920 --> 01:44:31,380
Wonder why... why... why!

883
01:44:36,100 --> 01:44:39,730
Just think about it,
there is only grief in love

884
01:44:41,100 --> 01:44:44,730
As for love's cruelty,
it's past counting

885
01:44:46,110 --> 01:44:50,240
When in love
your head must remain bowed

886
01:44:51,280 --> 01:44:55,410
Even when in pain
you have to smile

887
01:44:55,620 --> 01:44:58,750
Why fill your own life
with poison?

888
01:45:03,130 --> 01:45:06,420
Wonder why
people fall in love

889
01:45:08,460 --> 01:45:11,920
Wonder why,
Oh wonder why

890
01:45:13,470 --> 01:45:17,100
Wonder why why... why...

891
01:45:22,140 --> 01:45:28,280
Without love
what's left in life

892
01:45:29,650 --> 01:45:36,450
Without love
A person is Ionely

893
01:45:41,000 --> 01:45:44,300
Without love
what's there in life

894
01:45:44,830 --> 01:45:47,960
Without love
A person is Ionely

895
01:45:48,670 --> 01:45:51,800
Love brings colour
into your life

896
01:45:52,340 --> 01:45:55,640
Love brings beauty
into your life

897
01:45:56,180 --> 01:45:59,480
People fall in love
but hide it

898
01:46:03,690 --> 01:46:06,980
Wonder why they fear
expressing it openly

899
01:46:09,020 --> 01:46:12,480
Wonder why,
Oh wonder why...

900
01:46:13,860 --> 01:46:17,490
Wonder why why why!

901
01:47:05,410 --> 01:47:08,040
Love is just
needless trouble

902
01:47:10,250 --> 01:47:13,220
Love is beautiful
in every aspect

903
01:47:14,760 --> 01:47:18,210
We are all better off
far away from love

904
01:47:20,100 --> 01:47:23,220
Love's every form
is the assured truth

905
01:47:23,600 --> 01:47:27,900
He that tests love's
waters...

906
01:47:28,600 --> 01:47:31,730
...neither drowns nor floats

907
01:47:32,440 --> 01:47:34,740
Wonder why?

908
01:47:34,940 --> 01:47:38,070
Everyone but everyone
falls in love

909
01:47:38,450 --> 01:47:42,250
Wonder why only you
keep avoiding it

910
01:47:42,450 --> 01:47:46,250
Wonder why...

911
01:47:46,460 --> 01:47:48,580
Wonder why...

912
01:47:50,130 --> 01:47:54,080
Wonder why why why!

913
01:48:28,030 --> 01:48:28,830
Tell me something Shalini

914
01:48:29,860 --> 01:48:31,330
Why're you so scared of
sitting on these rides?

915
01:48:32,200 --> 01:48:33,000
I m not scared

916
01:48:34,370 --> 01:48:39,000
I think only those who aren't right
in their heads enjoy these rides

917
01:48:41,710 --> 01:48:42,340
Interesting excuse

918
01:48:43,210 --> 01:48:45,340
You need courage to sit on
these rides! You need guts

919
01:48:46,550 --> 01:48:48,850
But don't worry. There are many
cowards like you around here

920
01:48:50,050 --> 01:48:51,350
Look. There's one right there

921
01:48:56,220 --> 01:48:57,190
It's not like that at all

922
01:48:57,890 --> 01:49:02,020
If it isn't like that, then get on
that ride with me

923
01:49:07,070 --> 01:49:08,200
Why? No guts?

924
01:49:10,240 --> 01:49:10,860
It's getting late

925
01:49:16,750 --> 01:49:18,210
I'm going on that ride

926
01:49:18,920 --> 01:49:22,220
If you want, you can come with me.
Or sit here and get bored

927
01:49:28,660 --> 01:49:31,290
Absolutely no guts

928
01:50:30,450 --> 01:50:32,420
Hurry. We can catch this train

929
01:52:52,100 --> 01:52:54,220
Really Shalini! How could you
scare that poor old man!

930
01:53:09,480 --> 01:53:10,610
How did it go?

931
01:53:11,480 --> 01:53:14,110
Really well. They like my work

932
01:53:14,490 --> 01:53:17,940
And... they want me to
come back

933
01:53:18,990 --> 01:53:19,960
That's great

934
01:53:20,830 --> 01:53:21,790
When will you have to go?

935
01:53:22,490 --> 01:53:24,790
I've just returned and you're
asking about my leaving

936
01:53:27,670 --> 01:53:28,960
Did you talk to Sameer?

937
01:53:29,330 --> 01:53:29,960
No. Why?

938
01:53:30,670 --> 01:53:33,640
He came over the morning
you left

939
01:53:34,000 --> 01:53:35,300
He seemed very troubled

940
01:53:37,340 --> 01:53:40,310
What did he say?
- Nothing

941
01:53:49,850 --> 01:53:52,320
When did you get back?

942
01:53:55,860 --> 01:53:57,490
How are you? How's everything?

943
01:53:57,700 --> 01:53:59,160
Great. How are things with you
man?

944
01:53:59,530 --> 01:54:01,160
It's a very long story

945
01:54:01,530 --> 01:54:02,660
Let's go up and talk

946
01:54:07,500 --> 01:54:09,970
Okay, so here's the situation

947
01:54:11,340 --> 01:54:13,470
You are pretty good friends.
Hang out together

948
01:54:14,180 --> 01:54:15,640
But you still haven't told her
how you feel

949
01:54:17,350 --> 01:54:18,470
I've tried very hard...

950
01:54:21,850 --> 01:54:23,150
But the words just don't come out

951
01:54:27,360 --> 01:54:28,480
Didn't she have a boyfriend?

952
01:54:30,530 --> 01:54:32,150
Yup. She did... but not anymore

953
01:54:33,360 --> 01:54:35,160
I don't know what Pooja saw
in him

954
01:54:35,700 --> 01:54:38,170
I mean he was sweet
but what a bore!

955
01:54:40,700 --> 01:54:43,670
One day I made the mistake of
going for a drive with them

956
01:54:45,740 --> 01:54:46,710
See this place...

957
01:54:47,410 --> 01:54:50,040
I met Pooja for the first time
on 15th September right here

958
01:54:53,250 --> 01:54:56,710
Exactly 7 days later, we came here
to have ice cream... 22nd September

959
01:55:00,420 --> 01:55:01,720
You wouldn't remember the time,
would you?

960
01:55:02,260 --> 01:55:05,560
Of course I remember.
It was exactly 5.55

961
01:55:12,440 --> 01:55:14,730
That's not all

962
01:55:15,610 --> 01:55:18,730
He'd buy her a balloon
everyday

963
01:55:19,110 --> 01:55:19,730
Balloon...?

964
01:55:20,780 --> 01:55:25,240
Yes. You know those heart shaped
ones you get at signals

965
01:55:28,790 --> 01:55:31,250
It's okay but...
Everyday!

966
01:55:31,620 --> 01:55:32,420
One balloon a day!

967
01:55:37,930 --> 01:55:39,900
I knew the guy was deranged

968
01:55:50,110 --> 01:55:53,740
If you love Pooja so much,
why haven't you told her?

969
01:55:56,280 --> 01:55:57,410
I was afraid...

970
01:55:59,280 --> 01:56:02,250
What if Pooja says no?

971
01:56:04,120 --> 01:56:07,250
I'd even lose this friendship
we share now...

972
01:56:08,130 --> 01:56:09,090
and be all alone

973
01:56:14,130 --> 01:56:16,930
You weren't here.
Nor was Akash

974
01:56:23,470 --> 01:56:24,440
Anyway, you're here now

975
01:56:25,310 --> 01:56:27,280
And I feel stronger knowing
that you're here for me

976
01:56:28,650 --> 01:56:29,940
I'm always here for you, Sameer

977
01:56:33,980 --> 01:56:34,780
Then... shall I tell her today?

978
01:56:37,660 --> 01:56:38,280
Tell her

979
01:56:41,990 --> 01:56:44,120
Pooja, there's something
I need to tell you

980
01:56:47,160 --> 01:56:51,790
I wonder what if the arranging
incident hadn't happened

981
01:56:54,510 --> 01:56:57,300
If we hadn't met the way we
did...

982
01:56:58,180 --> 01:57:01,470
If I had met you somewhere else,
would we be the same as we are now?

983
01:57:02,180 --> 01:57:05,150
And if we weren't the way we are,
how else would we be?

984
01:57:05,520 --> 01:57:06,980
If you thought differently
about me...

985
01:57:07,180 --> 01:57:09,310
...if I thought differently about
you, what'd happen?

986
01:57:11,420 --> 01:57:15,050
What's happening now?
...What am I saying?

987
01:57:16,930 --> 01:57:22,230
Just a lot of ifs!
What's the matter?

988
01:57:25,270 --> 01:57:26,400
The matter is just that...

989
01:57:28,610 --> 01:57:29,730
I'm falling in love with you

990
01:57:32,450 --> 01:57:34,740
I agree that we don't know
each other very well

991
01:57:41,790 --> 01:57:45,920
If you trust me at all, believe
that I am telling the truth

992
01:58:29,600 --> 01:58:34,560
I look everywhere for her.
But I still haven't found her

993
01:58:34,770 --> 01:58:40,080
Where is the girl
in whose love I can believe?

994
01:58:44,950 --> 01:58:47,250
She who loves only me

995
01:58:47,450 --> 01:58:49,750
She must be even ready
to say...

996
01:58:49,960 --> 01:58:52,250
"O listen, you are the one
who has my heart"

997
01:58:52,460 --> 01:58:55,260
Oh, where is that girl?

998
01:59:04,970 --> 01:59:09,930
She who lives in your dream
as love's beautiful embodiment...

999
01:59:10,140 --> 01:59:12,440
You will find her someday
or other

1000
01:59:12,650 --> 01:59:15,610
Just look here and there

1001
01:59:20,320 --> 01:59:22,620
Let's both go and find her...

1002
01:59:22,820 --> 01:59:25,120
This angel, this fairy,
this damsel so dainty...

1003
01:59:25,330 --> 01:59:27,620
...who upon seeing,
you will say

1004
01:59:27,830 --> 01:59:30,630
She is right here!

1005
02:00:06,030 --> 02:00:09,660
I wonder why
I had this thought...

1006
02:00:10,370 --> 02:00:16,000
Could you be the
dream girl?

1007
02:00:16,210 --> 02:00:25,680
You have all the graces
that I search for everywhere

1008
02:00:25,890 --> 02:00:28,350
I think you are deluded

1009
02:00:28,550 --> 02:00:30,850
I wonder what you think I am

1010
02:00:31,060 --> 02:00:33,360
I am no angel or fairy
nor any celestial nymph

1011
02:00:33,560 --> 02:00:36,530
Don't have any such
illusions

1012
02:00:41,230 --> 02:00:46,040
I look everywhere for her.
But I still haven't found her

1013
02:00:46,240 --> 02:00:51,540
Where is the girl
in whose love I can believe?

1014
02:01:26,950 --> 02:01:30,910
Suppose I say to you...

1015
02:01:31,120 --> 02:01:36,920
All I think of
is you and only you

1016
02:01:37,120 --> 02:01:41,080
You must know
this is what I desire...

1017
02:01:41,290 --> 02:01:46,760
...you must be with me,
only with me

1018
02:01:46,970 --> 02:01:49,260
Oh, what have you made me believe!

1019
02:01:49,470 --> 02:01:51,770
Oh, how you make my heart beat!

1020
02:01:51,970 --> 02:01:54,270
You melt my body and soul...

1021
02:01:54,470 --> 02:01:57,270
...reciting this saga of yours

1022
02:02:07,150 --> 02:02:11,950
I look everywhere for her.
But I still haven't found her

1023
02:02:12,160 --> 02:02:14,960
Where is the girl
in whose love I can believe?

1024
02:02:15,160 --> 02:02:19,620
Oh, where is that girl?
That girl is here!

1025
02:02:19,830 --> 02:02:35,810
Where is that girl?
- That girl is here!

1026
02:03:03,540 --> 02:03:06,510
I can't believe that it's already
time for you to leave

1027
02:03:08,550 --> 02:03:10,520
Don't worry, Mom.
I'll be back soon

1028
02:03:11,050 --> 02:03:12,520
Three months is not soon

1029
02:03:14,050 --> 02:03:15,180
And that's this time

1030
02:03:17,060 --> 02:03:19,020
You don't know how long
you'll be gone next time

1031
02:03:22,060 --> 02:03:26,360
Siddharth... have you thought about
marriage?

1032
02:03:26,570 --> 02:03:27,190
Mom!

1033
02:03:29,070 --> 02:03:30,040
What Mom!

1034
02:03:32,570 --> 02:03:35,870
Some other time, okay?
- But why? Why not now?

1035
02:03:39,750 --> 02:03:44,380
It's just... forget it, Mom.
You won't understand

1036
02:03:47,090 --> 02:03:50,210
I'm your mother! If I can't
understand you, who else will?

1037
02:03:53,260 --> 02:03:54,380
Is there someone you like?

1038
02:03:59,770 --> 02:04:01,730
Sid, what's the matter?

1039
02:04:02,770 --> 02:04:04,400
You've never hidden anything
from me

1040
02:04:04,600 --> 02:04:07,070
Yes, Ma. But there are some things
that you just can't tell somebody

1041
02:04:07,440 --> 02:04:08,570
Yes there are...

1042
02:04:09,280 --> 02:04:12,570
But I can see there's something
eating away at you inside

1043
02:04:12,950 --> 02:04:15,070
Will you keep it bottled up inside
all your life?

1044
02:04:22,450 --> 02:04:24,080
Ma, I'm telling you
you won't understand!

1045
02:04:24,960 --> 02:04:26,080
Why won't I understand?

1046
02:04:27,460 --> 02:04:28,930
Try telling me

1047
02:04:32,630 --> 02:04:35,260
What is this thing that I don't
have the right to know?

1048
02:04:39,640 --> 02:04:40,260
What's the matter?

1049
02:04:52,650 --> 02:04:53,620
That Tara Jaiswal?

1050
02:04:56,390 --> 02:04:58,520
I've met her so many times...
But... she...

1051
02:05:01,230 --> 02:05:02,350
When did this start?

1052
02:05:03,560 --> 02:05:05,030
I don't know when...

1053
02:05:07,070 --> 02:05:08,690
I won't let you ruin your life!

1054
02:05:09,570 --> 02:05:11,700
Have you any inkling of what
you are saying?

1055
02:05:12,910 --> 02:05:14,870
My son has fallen in love with
a woman who...

1056
02:05:15,570 --> 02:05:17,200
You were right I wouldn't
understand

1057
02:05:18,740 --> 02:05:21,370
And what has she told you,
that she loves you?

1058
02:05:21,750 --> 02:05:24,380
She must've seduced you with her
sad stories

1059
02:05:25,020 --> 02:05:26,140
What did she say to you?
- She said nothing!

1060
02:05:32,690 --> 02:05:33,660
She doesn't even know that I...

1061
02:05:43,040 --> 02:05:44,830
Your mother is absolutely right,
Siddharth

1062
02:05:45,870 --> 02:05:50,830
Don't ruin your life over me. And the
little peace I have left in my life...

1063
02:05:51,710 --> 02:05:53,840
Please don't take it away
from me

1064
02:06:13,970 --> 02:06:16,940
Go away! - Please listen to me

1065
02:06:17,140 --> 02:06:18,110
I don't want to hear anything

1066
02:06:19,140 --> 02:06:22,440
Have I ever made you feel
that I love you...

1067
02:06:22,640 --> 02:06:24,270
...or want a relationship
with you?

1068
02:06:25,980 --> 02:06:26,450
No

1069
02:06:27,150 --> 02:06:28,620
Then what made you think...

1070
02:06:29,150 --> 02:06:30,280
...that you and I could...

1071
02:06:30,820 --> 02:06:32,120
...have any such relationship?

1072
02:06:35,990 --> 02:06:37,620
This is the problem with your
generation

1073
02:06:38,660 --> 02:06:43,790
You all think anything goes.
But that's not so, Siddharth

1074
02:06:47,000 --> 02:06:48,800
Why just me?

1075
02:06:49,670 --> 02:06:50,970
You have also caused your mother
a lot of pain

1076
02:06:53,510 --> 02:06:54,300
Please sit down

1077
02:07:24,540 --> 02:07:27,840
I'm so sorry that I caused you
and my mother such pain

1078
02:07:31,880 --> 02:07:34,180
I'm sorry you had to hear
all this because of me

1079
02:07:37,720 --> 02:07:39,690
But it's true that I love you

1080
02:07:53,530 --> 02:07:56,830
It's also true that I never
wanted you to know it

1081
02:07:59,010 --> 02:08:00,470
Because I knew that you...

1082
02:08:02,510 --> 02:08:03,310
...would never be able to understand

1083
02:08:08,750 --> 02:08:10,220
I just want to see you happy

1084
02:08:15,090 --> 02:08:20,050
And if knowing the truth
has caused you pain today...

1085
02:08:22,760 --> 02:08:26,060
All I can say is, that wasn't
my intention

1086
02:08:38,450 --> 02:08:41,570
Sid, please leave now

1087
02:09:16,080 --> 02:09:16,880
After the workshop...

1088
02:09:19,590 --> 02:09:22,060
I think I'll go stay at uncle's
farm house for a while

1089
02:09:24,260 --> 02:09:25,730
It's a good place to paint

1090
02:09:36,100 --> 02:09:37,230
Will you come with me?

1091
02:09:41,280 --> 02:09:42,740
I don't want to go without you

1092
02:10:21,320 --> 02:10:21,940
Just a minute...

1093
02:11:18,410 --> 02:11:19,370
You look very lovely

1094
02:11:25,080 --> 02:11:27,380
So, why are we here?

1095
02:11:28,750 --> 02:11:32,550
To prove to you that a thing called
love does exist in this world

1096
02:11:35,760 --> 02:11:37,050
Don't you ever give up?

1097
02:11:38,260 --> 02:11:39,890
Shut up and lets go in

1098
02:12:07,960 --> 02:12:10,250
Why are we here?
- To watch an opera

1099
02:12:11,630 --> 02:12:12,420
Yes, but why?

1100
02:12:13,790 --> 02:12:15,260
You'll know when the time comes

1101
02:13:22,700 --> 02:13:24,990
The girl's name is Cressida
and the boy is Troilus

1102
02:13:26,530 --> 02:13:28,330
They love each other very much

1103
02:13:47,560 --> 02:13:49,020
But Troilus must go now

1104
02:13:50,390 --> 02:13:52,360
He has to go to war for his country

1105
02:13:54,230 --> 02:13:56,700
Cressida is afraid something may
happen to him

1106
02:13:58,900 --> 02:14:01,030
Troilus is telling her
nothing will happen to him

1107
02:15:22,320 --> 02:15:27,950
This is the spirit of Troilus...
standing at heaven's gate

1108
02:15:29,660 --> 02:15:31,130
But he doesn't want to go inside

1109
02:15:33,830 --> 02:15:35,630
He is asking God for one day

1110
02:15:38,170 --> 02:15:39,960
He wants to meet Cressida for
one last time

1111
02:15:42,010 --> 02:15:45,300
And tell her how much he loves her

1112
02:15:48,680 --> 02:15:50,310
If he is given one day...

1113
02:15:51,850 --> 02:15:53,980
He is willing to die a thousand
deaths

1114
02:16:02,030 --> 02:16:03,650
Shut your eyes, Akash

1115
02:16:09,700 --> 02:16:10,170
Think...

1116
02:16:11,700 --> 02:16:12,170
Who is it...

1117
02:16:13,870 --> 02:16:17,330
...to spend that one day with, you
are willing to die a thousand deaths

1118
02:16:20,040 --> 02:16:21,010
Who is it, Akash?

1119
02:17:58,410 --> 02:17:59,710
No so easily!

1120
02:18:01,240 --> 02:18:03,540
You still haven't told me
who you saw

1121
02:18:06,250 --> 02:18:07,720
You seem quite sure that I
saw someone?

1122
02:18:08,420 --> 02:18:10,220
Yes. Because today for
the first time...

1123
02:18:10,420 --> 02:18:12,720
...you're talking less
and thinking more!

1124
02:18:24,670 --> 02:18:25,290
Then listen

1125
02:18:27,670 --> 02:18:28,300
I saw her...

1126
02:18:30,670 --> 02:18:31,300
And I felt...

1127
02:18:31,510 --> 02:18:34,140
...perhaps this is what
they call love

1128
02:18:41,680 --> 02:18:42,810
I wanted to touch her...

1129
02:18:45,190 --> 02:18:46,490
...hold her in my arms...

1130
02:18:49,690 --> 02:18:52,490
I saw such innocence
in her eyes...

1131
02:18:55,360 --> 02:18:56,490
...like I see in your eyes now

1132
02:19:01,200 --> 02:19:02,330
Her voice...

1133
02:19:02,710 --> 02:19:04,330
...had the kind of magic
your voice has

1134
02:19:06,540 --> 02:19:10,340
I can still feel the fragrance
of her breath...

1135
02:19:10,550 --> 02:19:12,010
...like I can feel
in your breath now

1136
02:19:14,180 --> 02:19:14,980
Who was she?

1137
02:19:26,400 --> 02:19:27,520
That fat opera singer!

1138
02:19:45,580 --> 02:19:51,880
Shalini, come inside... at once!

1139
02:20:46,480 --> 02:20:48,100
I think the two of you should
talk alone

1140
02:20:57,590 --> 02:21:00,060
Where had you gone?
- To the opera

1141
02:21:02,320 --> 02:21:03,120
With Akash!

1142
02:21:04,990 --> 02:21:07,290
How many times have I told you
not to meet him!

1143
02:21:10,670 --> 02:21:13,970
Rohit, will you keep telling me
all my life...

1144
02:21:14,170 --> 02:21:15,640
...who I should or should not meet!

1145
02:21:19,010 --> 02:21:19,630
Yes. I will

1146
02:21:20,340 --> 02:21:23,640
And you will never see Akash
again. You got that?

1147
02:21:30,190 --> 02:21:33,310
Rohit, I need some time to think
and you need it too

1148
02:22:53,910 --> 02:22:57,200
Shalini had called.
She said it's important

1149
02:23:09,590 --> 02:23:11,390
Hi, Rohit. It's Akash

1150
02:23:12,920 --> 02:23:15,220
Is Shalini there? She had called

1151
02:23:15,760 --> 02:23:19,560
I know. We are going back...
to get married

1152
02:23:25,270 --> 02:23:26,240
Can I speak to Shalini?

1153
02:23:54,200 --> 02:23:55,670
That's good news

1154
02:23:58,300 --> 02:23:59,930
Akash, we are going back tomorrow

1155
02:24:01,310 --> 02:24:02,770
Can you come for dinner tonight?

1156
02:24:05,810 --> 02:24:07,940
I don't know. Bye

1157
02:24:25,330 --> 02:24:26,460
Hey, Akash! We thought you
weren't going to make it

1158
02:25:09,140 --> 02:25:11,510
They're beautiful. Thanks

1159
02:25:13,210 --> 02:25:13,900
What will you drink?

1160
02:25:15,650 --> 02:25:18,910
We can drink later. Let's eat first.
I'm starving

1161
02:25:45,910 --> 02:25:48,710
Shalini, have you told
Mahesh Uncle...

1162
02:25:48,910 --> 02:25:50,380
...how you and Akash met?

1163
02:25:54,420 --> 02:25:54,940
No?

1164
02:25:57,720 --> 02:25:58,880
Really, Mahesh Uncle...

1165
02:25:59,460 --> 02:26:01,720
I don't know what you'd have
done if you were there

1166
02:26:01,930 --> 02:26:03,050
What happened?

1167
02:26:04,860 --> 02:26:06,560
It was at my graduation
party

1168
02:26:07,230 --> 02:26:07,890
Shalini was with me

1169
02:26:08,100 --> 02:26:10,160
Perhaps Akash didn't know
that...

1170
02:26:20,440 --> 02:26:21,740
Sorry for the punch

1171
02:26:25,120 --> 02:26:27,580
No, Rohit. It was my fault

1172
02:26:30,620 --> 02:26:33,590
But to tell you the truth,
I think I was lucky

1173
02:26:34,930 --> 02:26:35,410
What do you mean?

1174
02:26:35,760 --> 02:26:39,320
I mean, if Shalini was with me...

1175
02:26:40,300 --> 02:26:42,430
...and someone had acted fresh...

1176
02:26:44,140 --> 02:26:45,430
I'd have killed him

1177
02:26:58,950 --> 02:26:59,440
That is...

1178
02:27:00,790 --> 02:27:02,280
If Shalini was with you

1179
02:27:35,190 --> 02:27:35,780
Hey, wait...

1180
02:27:56,770 --> 02:27:59,330
You're coming to our wedding,
aren't you?

1181
02:28:00,380 --> 02:28:03,180
No, I can't make it. There's a lot
of work to be done

1182
02:28:05,520 --> 02:28:06,510
Some friend you are!

1183
02:28:08,120 --> 02:28:10,680
Anyway, don't forget to call us to
your wedding

1184
02:28:11,520 --> 02:28:12,350
We'll definitely be there

1185
02:28:13,260 --> 02:28:15,020
I'm not going to get married

1186
02:28:15,760 --> 02:28:16,350
Why?

1187
02:28:18,800 --> 02:28:21,360
It's necessary to love someone
to get married

1188
02:28:22,230 --> 02:28:23,700
And I believe...

1189
02:28:24,070 --> 02:28:25,870
...this thing called love doesn't
exist in the world

1190
02:28:28,470 --> 02:28:30,170
Shalini and I love each other

1191
02:28:30,410 --> 02:28:32,210
That's why we're getting married.
Isn't that so, Shalini?

1192
02:28:35,580 --> 02:28:40,210
You both shouldn't ask each other
this question. Ask yourself

1193
02:28:46,260 --> 02:28:47,050
I better go

1194
02:29:20,060 --> 02:29:22,250
You left your jacket with me
the other night

1195
02:29:36,140 --> 02:29:41,100
Some day I want to tell you why
I am marrying Rohit

1196
02:29:41,310 --> 02:29:45,270
Why? What's the need to tell me?

1197
02:29:47,950 --> 02:29:48,780
I need to...

1198
02:29:50,120 --> 02:29:51,780
Because we both know...

1199
02:29:54,890 --> 02:29:56,790
...that night at the opera,
when you shut your eyes...

1200
02:29:58,130 --> 02:30:00,620
...it wasn't the fat opera singer
you saw

1201
02:30:27,030 --> 02:30:33,660
Loneliness

1202
02:30:36,800 --> 02:30:41,170
This Ioneliness...

1203
02:30:46,650 --> 02:30:51,350
Why have I stumbled on
the path of love

1204
02:30:51,650 --> 02:30:56,180
All my dreams lie shattered
A sense of gloom lies heavy

1205
02:30:56,390 --> 02:31:00,850
Every joy is be numbed

1206
02:31:01,230 --> 02:31:06,290
My very life is lost

1207
02:31:06,570 --> 02:31:11,270
I am being punished
for loving you

1208
02:31:11,470 --> 02:31:16,340
Loneliness...

1209
02:31:16,780 --> 02:31:21,080
Loneliness stretches over
miles and miles

1210
02:32:10,630 --> 02:32:16,090
In my dream I saw
a hand in my hand

1211
02:32:20,640 --> 02:32:26,270
Now I am blinded by the
shards of a shattered dream

1212
02:32:40,490 --> 02:32:44,950
Someone was here yesterday

1213
02:32:45,170 --> 02:32:50,260
but today there is no one

1214
02:32:50,670 --> 02:32:55,470
Like a cobra's venomous hiss
it envelopes my very breath...

1215
02:32:55,680 --> 02:33:00,340
...this Ioneliness

1216
02:33:00,720 --> 02:33:04,910
has brought tears to my eyes

1217
02:33:54,900 --> 02:34:00,360
Oh how could my hope for
something be so futile

1218
02:34:04,840 --> 02:34:10,650
I've embarked on a journey
to which there is no destination

1219
02:34:24,430 --> 02:34:28,730
Where should I go?

1220
02:34:29,100 --> 02:34:34,200
To whom shall I explain?

1221
02:34:34,640 --> 02:34:36,730
What I had wanted...

1222
02:34:36,940 --> 02:34:39,240
And why I ended up with...

1223
02:34:39,450 --> 02:34:44,410
...this Ioneliness

1224
02:34:44,620 --> 02:34:48,750
Loneliness
deeply dark as the night

1225
02:34:59,270 --> 02:35:04,100
Why have I stumbled on
the path of love

1226
02:35:04,300 --> 02:35:08,740
All my dreams lie shattered
A sense of gloom lies heavy

1227
02:35:08,940 --> 02:35:13,610
Every joy is be numbed

1228
02:35:13,810 --> 02:35:19,120
My very life is lost

1229
02:35:19,420 --> 02:35:23,950
I am being punished
for loving you

1230
02:35:24,160 --> 02:35:28,820
Loneliness...

1231
02:35:29,330 --> 02:35:33,630
Loneliness stretches over
miles and miles

1232
02:36:20,880 --> 02:36:22,110
Hello, Aunty. Is Sameer home?

1233
02:36:22,450 --> 02:36:23,180
Who is this?

1234
02:36:27,090 --> 02:36:30,020
You want to talk to Sameer
and you've called Siddharth!

1235
02:36:31,090 --> 02:36:31,850
How are you?

1236
02:36:32,530 --> 02:36:34,360
I... I'm okay, Aunty

1237
02:36:34,960 --> 02:36:38,860
He's gone to Kasauli. Give me
your number. I'll give it to him

1238
02:36:40,530 --> 02:36:42,530
No, it's okay.
I'll call him

1239
02:37:36,590 --> 02:37:37,350
How are you, son?

1240
02:37:41,390 --> 02:37:42,050
I'm okay, Dad

1241
02:37:44,530 --> 02:37:47,830
What's wrong? Are you unwell?

1242
02:37:49,170 --> 02:37:50,190
No, it's nothing like that

1243
02:37:51,610 --> 02:37:52,940
Been working all day...

1244
02:37:53,310 --> 02:37:54,100
I'm tired, that's all

1245
02:38:06,420 --> 02:38:08,050
Come back home, Akash

1246
02:38:36,880 --> 02:38:37,820
What's wrong, Akash?

1247
02:38:40,090 --> 02:38:41,990
I've never seen you like this
before

1248
02:38:43,190 --> 02:38:44,250
I'm in love, Dad

1249
02:38:47,430 --> 02:38:50,120
So what's the problem?

1250
02:38:51,660 --> 02:38:53,150
She is marrying somebody else

1251
02:38:57,370 --> 02:38:59,840
Have you told her you love her?

1252
02:39:01,980 --> 02:39:02,460
No

1253
02:39:03,980 --> 02:39:05,410
Does she love you?

1254
02:39:09,850 --> 02:39:10,610
Yes, she does

1255
02:39:13,360 --> 02:39:14,480
Has she told you?

1256
02:39:20,700 --> 02:39:25,190
Akash, you must tell her
how you feel

1257
02:39:27,840 --> 02:39:28,300
No

1258
02:39:29,110 --> 02:39:29,700
Why not?

1259
02:39:33,110 --> 02:39:34,540
She is marrying somebody else

1260
02:39:38,580 --> 02:39:42,880
There are many things in this world
that are beyond our understanding

1261
02:39:44,050 --> 02:39:45,880
When a person decides something...

1262
02:39:47,090 --> 02:39:50,220
...there must be a reason for that
decision

1263
02:39:51,360 --> 02:39:56,590
You say that the girl loves you
but is marrying someone else

1264
02:39:57,930 --> 02:40:02,230
Have you tried to find out
why she's doing it?

1265
02:40:04,710 --> 02:40:06,800
What's the reason for her decision?

1266
02:40:25,990 --> 02:40:26,930
How's Shalini?

1267
02:40:28,760 --> 02:40:29,490
She isn't happy

1268
02:40:31,630 --> 02:40:32,600
And how could she be?

1269
02:40:33,770 --> 02:40:36,740
She is marrying Rohit
but loves you

1270
02:40:40,910 --> 02:40:42,570
Did she tell you that?
- No

1271
02:40:44,910 --> 02:40:46,640
Did you ever tell me you love her?

1272
02:40:52,120 --> 02:40:53,880
Then why's she getting married?

1273
02:40:56,690 --> 02:40:59,180
Rohit's father and Shalini's father
were business partners

1274
02:41:01,500 --> 02:41:06,430
Shalini was six when her parents
were killed in a car accident

1275
02:41:08,140 --> 02:41:13,040
I was her only relative but
I wasn't able to support her

1276
02:41:16,140 --> 02:41:17,370
Rohit's parents took her in...

1277
02:41:17,580 --> 02:41:18,140
...not only into their home

1278
02:41:18,350 --> 02:41:20,280
but their hearts and their life

1279
02:41:21,550 --> 02:41:23,040
They've done a lot for her

1280
02:41:24,150 --> 02:41:28,150
If they want her to marry Rohit,
Shalini can't refuse

1281
02:41:30,690 --> 02:41:31,920
What else can she do?

1282
02:41:33,700 --> 02:41:37,260
On one hand are the people who've
given her the life she's living

1283
02:41:38,770 --> 02:41:39,700
On the other hand is a man...

1284
02:41:39,900 --> 02:41:42,600
She doesn't even know if he loves
her or not

1285
02:41:43,770 --> 02:41:48,440
Akash, what are you doing man!
Go and tell her you love her

1286
02:41:52,110 --> 02:41:54,080
Akash, only you know what
you have to do

1287
02:41:55,580 --> 02:41:57,710
Just know this. Tonight is
the Sangeet function...

1288
02:41:59,050 --> 02:42:00,250
...and tomorrow the wedding

1289
02:42:02,530 --> 02:42:05,390
Whatever your decision,
you must make it today

1290
02:44:20,290 --> 02:44:21,350
Will you marry me?

1291
02:44:30,840 --> 02:44:33,470
Not even if I tell you that
I love you?

1292
02:45:14,880 --> 02:45:15,440
Shalini...

1293
02:45:17,450 --> 02:45:19,510
I love you and only you

1294
02:45:22,060 --> 02:45:23,080
My every breath...

1295
02:45:24,760 --> 02:45:25,850
...every heartbeat...

1296
02:45:27,630 --> 02:45:30,220
...every moment,
is for you, Shalini

1297
02:45:33,070 --> 02:45:38,230
I'm sure that I was born
so that I could love you

1298
02:45:39,740 --> 02:45:42,370
And you were born to become mine

1299
02:45:43,680 --> 02:45:45,040
You are mine, Shalini

1300
02:45:46,110 --> 02:45:47,880
And if you ask your heart...

1301
02:45:49,020 --> 02:45:52,110
...you will know that I speak
the truth

1302
02:45:59,090 --> 02:46:01,720
What's going on! Who is this boy?

1303
02:46:02,100 --> 02:46:02,890
I'll tell you

1304
02:46:04,100 --> 02:46:07,800
He is Akash Malhotra,
A.K. Malhotra's son...

1305
02:46:08,470 --> 02:46:10,730
...who's been after Shalini,
wagging his tail

1306
02:46:11,710 --> 02:46:15,400
I hit him once but I guess
it wasn't enough, huh?

1307
02:46:16,480 --> 02:46:17,600
I won't leave you today!

1308
02:46:17,810 --> 02:46:23,050
You will do no such thing, Rohit.
I want to speak to Shalini first

1309
02:46:52,350 --> 02:46:55,110
No, Rohit! You wait here.
- But Dad! This is my life...

1310
02:48:13,900 --> 02:48:17,560
Mahesh, I feel very hurt today

1311
02:48:18,740 --> 02:48:21,430
I always thought that Shalini was
my daughter

1312
02:48:22,340 --> 02:48:25,370
But today I feel that she has
never thought of us as her own

1313
02:48:27,610 --> 02:48:30,510
She wants to repay her debt to us
by marrying Rohit

1314
02:48:33,050 --> 02:48:33,540
All right

1315
02:48:36,920 --> 02:48:39,950
Shalini, you must repay us

1316
02:48:41,690 --> 02:48:45,390
For looking after you from
childhood till now... you owe us

1317
02:48:46,230 --> 02:48:49,060
For giving you whatever you
asked for... you owe us

1318
02:48:50,330 --> 02:48:53,270
For shielding you from
even a hint of trouble...

1319
02:48:53,370 --> 02:48:54,200
...you owe us

1320
02:48:56,270 --> 02:49:00,440
Now if you want to repay all that
you owe us... see us happy...

1321
02:49:03,410 --> 02:49:04,940
Then marry Akash

1322
02:49:11,760 --> 02:49:13,280
Can you do this much for me?

1323
02:49:33,440 --> 02:49:34,070
Come...

1324
02:49:45,420 --> 02:49:49,520
Take care of her.
She is my daughter

1325
02:50:25,060 --> 02:50:25,820
Just a minute, Dad

1326
02:50:28,200 --> 02:50:30,960
You can't do this! Mom, why
aren't you saying anything?

1327
02:50:31,600 --> 02:50:33,500
Let her go, Rohit

1328
02:50:36,810 --> 02:50:40,000
You care about Shalini's happiness
but don't give a damn about mine!

1329
02:50:40,310 --> 02:50:44,770
Rohit, if Shalini is not happy
being with you...

1330
02:50:45,420 --> 02:50:46,910
...how can you ever be happy?

1331
02:50:49,050 --> 02:50:50,210
This can't happen to me!

1332
02:50:53,960 --> 02:50:55,120
I won't allow this!

1333
02:50:58,530 --> 02:50:59,020
What are you doing?

1334
02:51:34,400 --> 02:51:36,020
I love Akash

1335
02:51:57,090 --> 02:51:58,320
All his life he said...

1336
02:51:58,620 --> 02:52:00,320
I won't say "I love you" to anyone

1337
02:52:00,760 --> 02:52:01,750
And when he had to say it...

1338
02:52:02,090 --> 02:52:04,960
It was at someone's wedding
in front of 300 people!

1339
02:52:09,270 --> 02:52:10,320
Did you call him?

1340
02:52:14,140 --> 02:52:14,970
What did he say?

1341
02:52:18,010 --> 02:52:19,000
He wasn't home

1342
02:52:24,680 --> 02:52:26,410
I told you he won't come

1343
02:54:19,800 --> 02:54:21,790
Can I talk to Sid?

1344
02:54:43,150 --> 02:54:43,920
How are you?

1345
02:54:45,720 --> 02:54:47,520
Fine. How are you?

1346
02:54:54,230 --> 02:54:55,390
Forgive me

1347
02:54:58,340 --> 02:54:59,860
I must apologise too

1348
02:55:01,100 --> 02:55:04,940
Some other time.
It's my turn today

1349
02:55:07,410 --> 02:55:08,670
You haven't changed
at all

1350
02:55:09,510 --> 02:55:13,450
Ya. Anyway, it's hard to improve
on perfection

1351
02:55:19,760 --> 02:55:21,120
Where are you? When can we meet?

1352
02:55:22,590 --> 02:55:26,190
Today. Now. This very moment

1353
02:57:04,530 --> 02:57:08,660
Now... there's no pain...
nor any fear

1354
02:57:13,140 --> 02:57:14,630
I feel good

1355
02:57:17,040 --> 02:57:18,030
It's peaceful here

1356
02:57:22,650 --> 02:57:24,780
You're a good boy, Siddharth

1357
02:57:28,820 --> 02:57:30,520
You always stood by me

1358
02:57:35,190 --> 02:57:36,850
You want me to be happy,
don't you...

1359
02:57:40,770 --> 02:57:41,930
Then... you be happy

1360
02:57:44,770 --> 02:57:45,530
You will, won't you?

1361
02:57:45,910 --> 02:57:46,460
I will

1362
02:57:57,420 --> 02:57:58,850
Life is so strange

1363
02:58:01,090 --> 02:58:02,490
Some relationships...

1364
02:58:05,690 --> 02:58:07,320
...don't have any name

1365
02:58:14,130 --> 02:58:16,160
You and I will always...

1366
03:00:13,020 --> 03:00:15,710
Hey Sid, look at your ship

1367
03:00:17,020 --> 03:00:19,510
It was so small 2 years ago.
Look how much it's grown

1368
03:00:22,800 --> 03:00:25,790
If you guys wanted to be by
yourselves, you should've told us

1369
03:00:29,030 --> 03:00:31,760
See! I'm getting told off because
of you

1370
03:00:31,970 --> 03:00:32,960
I've been telling you, let's go

1371
03:00:33,240 --> 03:00:33,730
What?

1372
03:00:34,410 --> 03:00:35,300
Come on

1373
03:01:03,600 --> 03:01:04,400
Come on man

1374
